cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the optimization of direct device-to-device (D2D) communications in cellular networks, which is a topic related to network infrastructure and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of channel and topology parameters, which suggests a possible fit with cs.IT (Information Theory). The use of context-awareness to adaptively exploit D2D communications is a topic that can be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also mentions the improvement of fairness, which is a topic that can be related to cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
